121.6	Ludwig_von_Mises	Ludwig von Mises	Ludwig Heinrich Edler von Mises (German pronunciation: ; September 29, 1881 â€“ October 10, 1973) was an Austrian economist, philosopher, and classical liberal who was a prominent figure in the Austrian School of economic thought. Fearing a Nazi take-over of Europe, Mises emigrated to New York in 1940. He published his magnum opus Human Action in 1949. Mises had a significant influence on the Libertarian movement that developed in the United States in the mid-20th century.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f0/Ludwig_von_Mises.jpg/220px-Ludwig_von_Mises.jpg
